CAPE TOWN - The Parliamentary ad hoc committee probing the South African Broadcasting Corporation board's fitness to hold office will resume its work on Friday morning. Former board chairpersons Ben Ngubane and Ellen Tshabalala will appear before the Members of Parliament. Both Ngubane and Tshabalala have been mentioned by several witnesses who've testified before the committee. It has been alleged that the pair supported Hlaudi Motsoeneng's rise to power at the public broadcaster. READ: SABC board inquiry to resume on Friday MP’s are expected are to grill the former board chairs on a number of issues, including Motsoeneng’s permanent appointment as Chief Operations Officer. Ngubane and Tshabalala are the last two witnesses expected to testify before the committee compiles a draft report. eNCA